<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1381" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1381">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/225.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hamm</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Arrived Torreon last Monday. Everything is still chaotic. In several
                                interviews with Commander in Chief he has promised to protect all
                                foreign property with the exception of Spaniards towards whom and
                                their interests he is absolutely uncompromising. States all
                                Spaniards must leave sections of the Republic under his control. I
                                made especial plea for the Durango Spaniards which was unheeded. A
                                great many flagrant cases confiscation abandoned Spanish property
                                already occurred in Torreon and vicinity.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamm</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>